{
  "texts": [
    "The case study not only enhances our understanding of the computational challenges inherent in real-time collision detection but also highlights the importance of WCET analysis in ensuring the reliability and efficiency of robotic operations.",
    "Estimating WCET Using GATo accurately measure WCET, it is necessary to execute the algorithm across all possible inputs and record the execution time for each.",
    "However, considering the vast input space of the collision detection algorithms running the algorithm for every possible input is not feasible in practice.",
    "Therefore, we employ the GA [104] to generate inputs in a manner guided by two defined fitness functions: one based on execution time and the other on the diversity of inputs.",
    "We aim to efficiently explore the input space of the algorithm within the constraints of limited exploration time."
  ]
}